Description: Fragment of flattened handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '134̣'. Name Phanias. Possibly a recut die.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (215)
